The paper deals with object counting and instance segmentation, which are both topics in computer vision. The use of density maps and limited object count information also suggests a focus on machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves training and optimization of models, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the use of psychological studies to motivate their approach, which could potentially fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language).
